<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How PianoAi collects, uses, and protects your information."
  updated="June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how PianoAi ("we", "us", or "our") collects,
    uses, and shares information when you use our mobile application and
    related services (the "App").
  </p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Account information</strong> — such as your name, email
      address, and login credentials when you create an account.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Audio input</strong> — with your permission, the App accesses
      your device's microphone to listen to your piano playing so it can
      provide real-time feedback on notes, timing, and rhythm.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Practice and progress data</strong> — including songs
      practiced, exercises completed, scores, and streaks.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Device and usage information</strong> — such as device type,
      operating system, app version, and general usage analytics.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide, operate, and improve the App's core features</li>
    <li>
      Analyze your playing in real time to generate feedback and
      recommendations
    </li>
    <li>Personalize your practice path and song recommendations</li>
    <li>Maintain the security and reliability of our services</li>
    <li>Communicate with you about your account or the App</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Microphone and Audio Data</h2>
  <p>
    Audio captured by the App is used solely to analyze your performance and
    provide feedback. Audio processing may occur on your device or be sent
    securely to our servers for analysis. We do not use your audio
    recordings for advertising purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Share Information</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with
    service providers who help us operate the App (such as cloud hosting and
    analytics providers), or when required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention and Security</h2>
  <p>
    We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as
    needed to provide the App's services. We use reasonable technical and
    organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized
    access, loss, or misuse.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Choices</h2>
  <p>
    You can control microphone access through your device settings at any
    time. You may also request access to, correction of, or deletion of your
    personal information by contacting us through our
    <a href="/support">Support page</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The App is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly
    collect personal information from children under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you
    of significant changes by updating the "Last updated" date above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please visit our
    <a href="/support">Support page</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
